American Enterprise Institute expert Christina Sommers, author of “Who Stole Feminism?”, told She The People that young men in the United States, especially young men of color, are “much more vulnerable than their sisters,” but Steinem’s comments to Ferguson’s party face criticism she has raised previously.
We now have hundreds of special programs for girls and young women, but almost none for boys.
But when the White House launched a small My Brother's Keeper program to help vulnerable young blacks and Hispanics, it sparked angry reactions from many feminists, including Gloria Steinem.
The police’s relationship with the black community is not the only issue that comes to the forefront of mainstream feminism.
