Around 23,000 people in the UK are thought to suffer from CMT, which can manifest as motor symptoms such as muscle weakness, clumsy walking and twisted toes.
Affected people may also experience numbness or pain, this condition is incurable and progressive, which means that over time the symptoms get worse.
When Rodgers was thirteen, she thought she was suffering from Freidreich ataxia (FA), a disease that has a very poor prognosis.
