When Rodgers was thirteen, and after several surgeries to relieve her Achilles tendons and straighten her feet, she took advantage of her doctor’s leaving the room, and looked into her documentation to find out that she was suffering from FA.
“I felt guilty because I was snooping, so I didn’t tell anyone, but when I got home, I looked up information about the disease in the library and wrote to the FA Association,” he says.
