They were allegedly gained through unauthorized access to user accounts on Apple’s servers, which the affected users uploaded through automatic backup of images from iPhones and iPads.
Apple has not yet commented on the issue.
Some celebrities reject the images as fake, but several have already admitted the authenticity of the images.
They include actress Jennifer Lawrence, known for her role as Katniss in the Hunger Games film series, and Mary Elizabeth Winstead, who starred in Die Hard 4.0, for example.
The goal of the hacker is to use the acquired images and videos to enrich.
According to reports on 4chan, the hacker is reportedly interested in the footage, but he prefers to get money from the community.
According to The Next Web, it’s very likely a vulnerability in iCloud’s security.
Two days ago, a tool appeared on the GitHub server that allowed you to get passwords to user accounts through brute force, that is, by automatically repeating login attempts with different passwords.
This tool was proven to work, but Apple closed the security hole after two days.
What is certain, however, is that potential attackers had plenty of time to gain access to various accounts before publishing this tool.
As a precautionary measure, iCloud users should change their Apple ID password.
What is important is the length of the password, not its complexity.
A length of at least 12 characters is appropriate.
The leak of nude celebrity photos is seen as a reminder of the safe use of online services.
Although the servers of companies such as Apple, Google or Microsoft are much better secured than computers in homes or smaller businesses, uploading sensitive photos in unprotected form is an unnecessary risk.
If you want to back up explicit photos or any other sensitive content online, first encrypt the files before uploading.
It is also wise to set up automatic backup of photos from the phone so that it only takes place on wi-fi and when connected to the charger.
Thus, you will be able to move sensitive images "to safety" in a timely manner, and most importantly, you will have the space to delete the failed images, so they will not unnecessarily occupy space in the online storage.
